::TF1::
Morphology uses shape-based operations on binary or grayscale images.
{TRUE}

::TF2::
Erosion shrinks objects in a binary image.
{TRUE}

::TF3::
Dilation makes objects grow in a binary image.
{TRUE}

::TF4::
Opening is erosion followed by dilation.
{TRUE}

::TF5::
Closing is dilation followed by erosion.
{TRUE}

::TF6::
Morphology is only applied to grayscale images, not binary images.
{FALSE}

::TF7::
Connected components labeling identifies groups of connected pixels.
{TRUE}

::TF8::
4-connectivity considers only horizontal and vertical neighbors.
{TRUE}

::TF9::
8-connectivity considers horizontal, vertical, and diagonal neighbors.
{TRUE}

::TF10::
Connected components can be used to count objects in an image.
{TRUE}

